Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a neural network architecture for visual saliency detection. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the model utilizes neurophysiologically plausible mechanisms for extraction of salient regions. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the model is a form of AI that simulates the bottom-up processes of human selective attention. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the model uses PCA implemented by means of normalized Hebbian learning. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the model through a psychological experiment.
